They mapped automation scores to nearly 2000 occupations in the US, UK, Canada and Australia and categorised

136
13:29.640 --> 13:36.560
those occupations into 15 business functions across 16 industry sectors.

137
13:36.630 --> 13:42.450
This mapping allowed them to understand how applicable automation was to different economies, sectors and

138
13:42.450 --> 13:44.500
business functions.

139
13:45.030 --> 13:52.020
As we can see, the 3 functions with the highest automation potential is: Finance, Administration and

140
13:52.020 --> 13:55.440
Customer Service. In the finance function

141
13:55.440 --> 14:02.910
it is estimated that 80% of tasks hold potential for automation. In the administration,

142
14:02.910 --> 14:07.680
the number is 79% and in customer service 75%.

143
14:07.680 --> 14:15.060
Note that this is potential across more technologies; both RPA, chatbots, machine learning (ML), natural language

144
14:15.060 --> 14:18.270
understanding (NLU) and machine vision was part of the survey.

145
14:18.540 --> 14:24.780
But these functions are probably a good starting point for having workshops and finding processes with an

146
14:24.780 --> 14:30.640
automation potential and start the work with creating a long list of opportunities (in your firm).